    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "07d720dc_a50d0eb7",
        "filename": "infra-sk/modules/page_object/page_object_element.ts",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 91,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-08T00:37:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "AFAIK there\u0027s not much to be done on the TypeScript front, since any typing information is lost after compilation, and we\u0027re talking about a runtime assertion.\n\nThe closest thing I can think of is asserting that el.tagName equals \"INPUT\", or \"SELECT\", or \"TEXTAREA\", etc. But that will limit us if we later decide to actually emulate individual key presses a la Puppeteer\u0027s ElementHandle#type()[1] method or WebDriver\u0027s setValue()[2] method, which can work for any element and not just input, selects, etc.\n\nSo I\u0027ll leave it as is for now. We can always add an explicit check later if we find this inconvenient while writing tests.\n\n[1] https://pptr.dev/#?product\u003dPuppeteer\u0026version\u003dv5.0.0\u0026show\u003dapi-elementhandletypetext-options\n[2] https://webdriver.io/docs/api/element/setValue.html",
      "parentUuid": "77e194ce_60c12be7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 91,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 91,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "924e7221b337648179b21b7f2e4b6e1dc350bba3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
