      "writtenOn": "2020-07-06T21:48:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Summary of our chat:\n\n- Our current tests simulate input events in this fashion in multiple places. The rationale is to capture that pattern here so we don\u0027t have to repeat it on each PageObject subclass.\n- In the future we might want to use Puppeteer\u0027s type() method[1], which sends keydown/keyup/etc events for each key press.\n- Thus, moving the event emulation logic upstack just for the DOM \"backend\" might be awkward in the future.\n- If in the future we find event emulation to be problematic for some tests, we can add an optional argument to this method to opt out of event emulation.\n\n[1] https://pptr.dev/#?product\u003dPuppeteer\u0026version\u003dv5.0.0\u0026show\u003dapi-pagetypeselector-text-options",
      "parentUuid": "79e311bd_abdbaa1c",
      "range": {
