      "lineNbr": 151,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-06T21:48:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure that the \"ToSelector\" bit would make it clearer, because all $-prefixed functions take a selector as their first argument.\n\nMaybe $$applyFn would make more sense, but I\u0027m hesitant to add the \"Fn\" suffix because all $-prefixed functions (except $ and $$) take a function as their second argument.\n\nThat\u0027s why I settled with $$apply.\n\n(FTR, I named it \"apply\" as in Function.prototype.apply()[1].)\n\nWDYT?\n\n[1] https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/apply.",
      "parentUuid": "2c638f26_a6039db8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 151,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 151,
        "endChar": 15
