        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-07T02:02:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oops, that was incorrect. I am in fact using this in downstream CLs.\n\nThe difference is that a function passed to $$apply takes a PageObjectElement as a parameter, whereas a function passed to $$evalDom takes an HTMLElement (i.e. a raw DOM node) as a paramter.\n\n$$apply is useful for things that can be done directly against the PageObjectElement API, for example clicking a specific button:\n\n  // This calls PageObjectElement#click().\n  await pageObjectElement.$$apply(\u0027button.submit\u0027, (btn) \u003d\u003e btn.click())\n\n$$evalDom is useful for operations against the raw DOM node, for example checking the value of a property in a custom component:\n\n  // Retursn the value of the element-sk\u0027s CheckOrRadio component\u0027s \"checked\" property.\n  const checked \u003d await this.$$evalDom(\u0027checkbox-sk\u0027, (c) \u003d\u003e (c as CheckOrRadio).checked);",
      "parentUuid": "b95fae77_d21aaab1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 164,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 164,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "924e7221b337648179b21b7f2e4b6e1dc350bba3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
